Emi's art is from the artist Oreteki18kin, the set -

Nakayoshi Chinpo Share

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUEmi
Recommended tags - black hair, short hair, brown eyes, blunt bangs, medium breasts,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag. Also, huge or large, take your pick on how "endowed" she should be.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

The biggest flaw I've encountered so far while using this little beast is that it has a hard time generating sex scenes. Other than that, I really enjoy using it.

Recommended settings are as follows:

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

Sampling steps: 20~30

VAE: the one that comes with SD 1.5

CFG Scale: 7~11

Excessively long negative prompts tend to make the output worse, not better, and most negative embeddings do more harm than good too. Keep the negative prompt nice and simple.
